File-LinkDir-OO

Create links in one directory for files in another.

This is a scriptable, object oriented approach to File::LinkDir's 
functionality. In addition, File::LinkDir::OO adds the ability to
use hard links.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc File::LinkDir::OO

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=File-LinkDir-OO

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/File-LinkDir-OO

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/File-LinkDir-OO

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/File-LinkDir-OO/


